    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "thanks. when u say \"short-term operational hurdles,\" that sounds like a pretty big deal for a small shop trying to stay afloat. are there specific ways these regs tend to hit their bottom line harder than bigger corporations? like is it mostly just the equipment costs or is there more to it?",
